              <p>3. <strong>Personalized Spaces</strong>: Buyers are looking for properties with bespoke design elements such as home theaters, indoor pools, and private gyms that reflect their tastes and lifestyles.</p>
              <p>4. <strong>Investment Potential</strong>: Luxury properties tend to appreciate over time, making them a sound investment for many buyers. Real estate in prestigious neighborhoods often holds its value better during economic downturns.</p>
              <p>5. <strong>Sustainable Luxury</strong>: There is a growing trend towards eco-friendly luxury homes that integrate sustainable materials and energy-efficient technologies, catering to environmentally conscious buyers.</p>
